I read all the negative reviews before getting this game but I bought it anyway to see for myself. That was in early December. I still havent been able to get a good save going yet despite my best efforts. For some unknown reason, the better the club you choose, the more injuries you get. (Anything from 1-4 injuries a game in the Prem). Anyone who has played previous versions of the game will know that the interface has always been a bit boring but really easy and handy to know where everything is. In 15, they've taken into account the slightly uninspiring interface but have shuffled it all about really badly and you have to re-learn where everything is, the main top bar has been moved to the left side of the screen...it's just confusing. FM 15 takes their 'You will concede 2 or 3 in stoppage time' rule to the next level, its virtually impossible to hold on to a lead. It doesn't matter if your team has great composure, bravery, team work, concentration etc, you will always concede goals in the final minutes. Basically, if your team is 1-0 up at the 75th minute mark, you may as well turn your computer off. I was playing as Man City. On three occasions I was 1-0 up in the 85th minute. I did three different things each time. 1st game - I dropped back and defended my lead. I lost 2-1. (Vs Stoke) 2nd game - I pushed up and uninvited pressure, I played the offside trap. I lost 3-1 (Vs West Brom) 3rd game - I changed to a 6-5-0. Every player on the pitch went into a defensive position to block the goal. I lost 2-1. (Vs Crystal Palace) It happens 9/10 times. Fair enough but when it happens so frequently its just screams 'broken'. You end up losing your lead in a burst of sudden energy from the other team. What makes it happen? Its almost half scripted. If im ahead at half time I always think to myself 'It doesnt matter, ill still lose'. I downvote this game because it is simply against you. Not in a challenging way but in more of a ' you' way.
