I played the demo first, then played the free weekend, so although I only have a few hours gameplay in FM15, I have over 200 each in FM14, 13,12,11,10 and 09, so I'd like to think that I know what I'm looking at. Despite my obvious love for the series, I cannot recommend this game/edition for this very simple reason..... Ideas: Good. Execution: Poor. The ideas/updates that SI have implemented into the game, such as expanded conversations and tactics are good in principle, but the execution of them has been poor to say the least. As just one example, many times I was presented with a response that caused players to react in completely the opposite way that the response dictates that they should. Even now, the injury problem hasn't been properly fixed, despite it being 8/9 months since the game was released. The AI/Match Engine simply cannot defend, and this isn't a tactical issue. The goalkeepers refuse to pick up the ball from no more than 5 yards away, and instead insist on waiting for another player to touch the ball before reacting to it. If you have FM14 already, then update the leagues etc using the many mods in the workshop and avoid FM15. If you don't have FM14, buy FM14 and just wait for FM16 to come out. Overall, FM14 despite having some issues of it's own, is a far less "Broken" game than FM15 is, and the problems that SI didn't fix themselves with FM14, the community has.
