I have been reading through the reviews for this game, yet I can't understand how people have said how rubbish they thing this new release is? Of course it's going to have some bugs/faults/issues with the game as soon as it comes out, just like any other PC game you buy, none are perfect as soon as they're released due to companies being pushed to release their games quicker so that they ensure they make a fast profit. You just need to be patient, like I was. Once the bugs were fixed and it was all how it was supposed to be, this is a really good game. Probably the best one out of the FM series yet, due to you have to actually Scout and search for certain player that you want/need. Instead of their being a huge list of transfer listed players available, so it's hit and miss on whether you get bargains or you end paying the full price. Which is extrememly realistic. The 3D graphics have been improved making it more realistic on the pitch especially with the new "Team Talk" feature allowing you to shour specific instructions to your team. The only downside is that Sega have yet again tried and failed with the Media, I started of as a Conference North Team (Chorley FC) yet i have press conferences before and after EVERY game. Surely a team that has only just made it to the Conference north, shouldn't be having this many Press Conferences/Tunnel Interviews if they haven't even been fully estabilished by anyone hardly? It just makes it seem like they haven't put much thought into the media. Overall I am pretty much on this game all the time now, it's extrememly addicting, I would advice anyone to purchase this. Plus 30 for a Pc game is nothing these days? BARGAIN.
