It's wierd at first and the default skin is terrible but after a few hours into it you start to get used to it. Scouting is actually allot more important than ever now and you go into your scouting tab in order to search for players that are transfer listed etc, based on your scouting knowledge. You can see how everything is working allot more now and makes it important to have feeder clubs from different countries to improve scouting knowledge across the globe. Touchline instructions are cool in theory but i found it to be pointless and makes your team worse off, just stick with the pre match and half time team talks. Match engine is allot better and it feels more fluid with the animations however are there some dodgy stuff that happens especially when 2 or 3 defenders are trying to chase down a loose ball then none of them end up getting it and leave it whilst a surging striker latches onto it and scores when they shouldent of had any chance of getting it. The only bad thing really for me is the default skin but that's a personal thing, as for the game it's solid and a solid upgrade. If you've not got a FM game for a while then deffo pick this up, if you get them every year then you should see more improvements this year than you have the previous years to warrent getting it aswell.
