Not sure why so many people are down-voting it. Having spent an extensive amount of time playing FM15, I can safely say there are bugs, but none of them game-breaking. I haven't noticed having more injuries than i'd expect. If you know what FM15 is about and have played old versions, then it's certainly worth a purchase. The level of detail and tinkering that's available to you is fantastic. If you want to take over Chelsea and win the CL or take over a lower league club and take them to the next level, it's all available for you here. I'm a football coach IRL and this is the most realistic football game you'll ever find (until FM16 anyway!). I'd give it a 9.5/10 If you're only going to play this for less than an hour or know nothing about "soccer" or think this is a FIFA clone, then i'd go find another game.
