Well just about finished the free weekend and I have to write about FM15 that I still cannot make up my mind on purchasing it! The game is a deep mineshaft of detail that can get you hooked if you like that level of detail but if you want to build Gainsborough Trinity from the depths to the Premiership within the game you are going to have no life outside of playing this game. The graphics are okay but not special on matchday (players do still wonder around a lot), the detail and depth are nice but you need time to learn the processes and where things are. I suppose the same can be said for most games but this has been taken to a fine art (or torture level) in this game. The last one of these games I purchased was FM10 and I refused to purchase another one until I could see some improvement in the match engine. Here I feel let down by FM15. Players running backwards was always a bugbear of mine. (Bug being the right word!). For me the depth would take time to learn and it may be worth paying the tenner now but having bought Train Fever I haven't the time at the moment for this game. The question is will it come on sale again? Probably not until FM16 comes out. If you have the patience, time and want to be a Football Manager then this could be right for you. For me I am undecided! PS For the people who call this Soccer not Football all can say is where are all the American Football Management games because I would love to make the Redskins the World Champions! (Don't laugh too loud!)
