TL;DR: Buy it if you want to manage a football team and either love the series or haven't played in a few seasons. It isn't perfect, but you'll get mileage from it. I would recommend this annual update if you haven't bought the last 1 or 2 Football Managers. If you have bought them all, like me, then you probably don't need a review. I wouldn't say that it is flawless though. Players seem to pick up injuries and knocks that put the out of the current game a little too often when compared to my watching of football out in the wilds of real life. Maybe that's because I start with low league teams, however, and may improve with the skill of my staff in later game play. I also find it frustrating that you can employ staff to delegate tasks to, but then find that the most simple tasks evade them. For example I had a director of football who continued to sign players even though we were already over our clubs wage limit. I can avoid this by either not recommending players or by leaving the contract signing to me, but it feels like a waste of time to delegate only part of what a staff member's role should be to that staff member. Again this might be because I start at low league (English Conference South), but it seems a bit awkward that they can't even do basic sums. The rest of the game is tight and I enjoy the micromanagement of the team, right down to the training. I also find some information into the development of the players easier to navigate to than before. I could probably write a lot more, but I find online reviews easier when they are terse and to the point.
Buy this game for someone you never want to see in your life again. :)
