Regarding a lot of these negeative reviews, I honestly do not know what game people have been playing. The new side bar is a massive improvement to FM's accessability. Each core page is now much easier to access, freeing up space for a large search bar to instantly find any player, cup or competition in the game's database. The new report page is excellent. It is now as clear as it can be what the pros and cons of each player are, making it even easier to scout the perfect player for your team in a given situation. As for the match engine, it keeps getting better and better each year and FM 2015 marks a big step forward with motion capture animations added to the mix. How anyone can play in 2D when the engine quality has improved so dramatically since its implementation is beyond me. FM 2015 is the biggest leap forward in the series for the past 2-3 years.
