Fun and Worth.
The title of the game is misleading. It should be called Football Watcher 2015. Every match seems to play out a certain way for the full 90, regardless of what you or the opponent do. I'm not saying it's scripted, but tactical changes don't alter the match at all. Also, about realism, certain tactics automatically work with any team, even though they make no sense at all, or always fail even though they have been proven to work well in real life. Just look at the tactics uploaded to the Steam Workshop. There are things like 2-5-3 or 3-4-3 which would fail horribly in real football, but work in this game because they exploit the weaknesses of the programming. It's not all negatives, though. Outside of matches, the game is excellent. The level of detail in transfers, contracts, training, player interaction, etc. is amazing. If I could, I would recommend the menus, but not the match simulation itself.
Still the best football simulator game.. After I missed the 2014 series, this 2015 series is a much improvement from 2013 series.. The most improved part is: (1) higher complexity in handling players' contracts and negotiation with other clubs; as well as (2) the improved tactical variety (player's role, etc). While this could be a little bit cumbersome for those who new to this series, I believe the built-in tutorial will be very useful.
