This game, in a word, is *addictive*. I find myself losing hours to this spreadsheet simulator, which to all my better judgement seems to be a random number generator which calculates football scores, completely detatched from the rest of the tactical, managerial business behind the scenes. And yet there is a chance that the tweaks you make to the team that lost 2-1 last time away to Brentford, would transform the team into Chelsea beaters and take you to the FA cup final and win glory for your beloved team. And that emotional empathy this game creates is as close to the real thing as watching a real football match on the TV. Superb.
